Privacy Policy for Tolmate Smart Weight Solution

Thank you for choosing Tolmate Smart Weight Solution! We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring a safe and secure user experience. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and share your information when you use our app, Tolmate.

1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information
We do not collect any personally identifiable information unless you explicitly provide it to us. Examples include:

Name and Contact Information: If you choose to create an account, we may collect your name, email address, and other details to personalize your experience.
Health Data (Optional): If provided, Tolmate may collect weight-related information to help track progress over time.
1.2 Usage Data
We may automatically collect information about your device and usage patterns to improve our app’s functionality and performance:

Device Information: Type of device, operating system, unique device identifiers, and IP address.
App Usage: Pages visited, features used, and time spent on the app to analyze and optimize the user experience.
1.3 Location Data
Tolmate may request permission to access your device’s location to provide features that rely on location-based services. Location data is optional and only used to enhance app functionality.

2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected data to:

Improve, personalize, and expand the functionality of the Tolmate app.
Monitor and analyze usage to enhance user experience.
Communicate with you regarding updates, support, and personalized recommendations.
Tolmate will not use your data for any purpose other than providing you with a safe and effective app experience.

3. Sharing and Disclosure of Information
Tolmate values your privacy, and we do not share, sell, or rent your information to third parties, except as required:

With Your Consent: If you choose to share your data with third-party integrations, we will request your explicit consent.
For Legal Requirements: If required by law, regulation, or government authority, we may disclose information to comply with legal obligations.
4. Data Retention and Security
We retain your data only as long as necessary to provide the services outlined in this policy. Tolmate implements commercially reasonable measures to secure your data from unauthorized access, disclosure, or destruction.

However, please note that no method of electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

5. Your Privacy Choices
Account Information: You may update or delete your account information at any time through the app settings.
Location and Device Data: You can control app permissions, including location and device data, through your device’s settings.
Data Deletion: If you wish to delete all your data permanently, please contact us at otamation@gmail.com.
6. Children's Privacy
Tolmate does not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from children under the age of 13. If we discover any data collected from children under 13 without verified parental consent, we will delete it promptly.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any changes.

8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or Tolmate’s data practices, please contact us at:

Email: pawan@otamation@gmail.com

